description: Category: Moon (Satellite, Planet Earth, Solar System). Session: 12 Dec 2016. Find me here: Instagram | Facebook The Moon is Earth's only permanent natural satellite. It is one of the largest natural satellites in the Solar System, and the largest among planetary satellites relative to the size of the planet that it orbits (its primary). It is the second-densest satellite among those whose densities are known (after Jupiter's satellite Io).
